item.title: CVE-2023-25950|2024-08-02T11:39:06.556Z -- haproxy%20technologies -- haproxy
item.description: HTTP request/response smuggling vulnerability in HAProxy version 2.7.0, and 2.6.1 to 2.6.7 allows a remote attacker to alter a legitimate user's request. As a result, the attacker may obtain sensitive information or cause a denial-of-service (DoS) condition.
